 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P01-T058 (cross-source entity resolution; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Fifty-eighth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S5-P01). Unifies the entities that appear across boards -- agencies, institutions, authors, companies, regions, topics, standards -- so the same real-world entity referred to differently by different sources resolves to one entity, without losing provenance and without being irreversible. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a deterministic resolver, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/entity_resolver.py provides the entity schema (entity_id, type, canonical_name, aliases, provenance, confidence, merged_from), resolve (cluster mentions by shared alias, each alias kept with its source), merge (a deepcopy `before` snapshot plus an audit; a merge below the confidence boundary AUTO_MERGE_MIN=0.80 is held for review, not auto-applied), split (reverse a merge exactly from the snapshot), and provenance_of. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T058/: entity_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T058/test-results/entity_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): 7 cross-source mentions resolve to 4 entities, unifying aliases from different sources (a standalone NBS from a media source joins 国家统计局 from stats-gov, 国办 joins 国务院办公厅, 发改委 joins 国家发展和改革委员会); a wrong merge is exactly reversible, since split restores both pre-merge entities byte-for-byte; every alias carries a source (nothing unsourced) and provenance_of covers all aliases; and the confidence boundary holds, since a merge with confidence 0.5 is held pending_review while one at 0.95 is applied. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S5-P01-T057 (Canonical Event aggregation; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Fifty-seventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program, opening Stage S5 (Multi-board Depth & Benefit Parity), S5-P01. Aggregates the original text, interpretations, reposts, and reactions of the same policy/event into ONE canonical event, so one event yields one alert rather than 20, while every member page stays individually expandable as evidence. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a deterministic aggregation tool, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/canonical_event.py provides the event identity (the shared event key -- an original's document number, or the document number a repost/interpretation references; no fuzzy title-only merging), primary selection (the most authoritative member whose own id is the event key, ordered A0 > A1 > A2 > media), and member links (every page kept individually retrievable with its role). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T057/: event_report.json, event_fixture.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S5-P01-T057/test-results/event_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): 20 pages about the same event (a real document number 苏政办函〔2026〕39号 from the T050 Jiangsu backfill as the original, plus 19 interpretations/reposts/reactions that cite it) aggregate to exactly 1 canonical event and 1 alert; all 20 members stay individually expandable and match the 20 source pages exactly; the primary is the A1 official original, not a media repost; and a no-over-merge control confirms a different event (a different document number 鲁科字〔2023〕143号) stays a separate event and event 1 absorbs none of its pages. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
